DPRK Footballers Win at AFC Soccer Championship 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The DPRK team won at the AFC Under-19 Soccer Championship held in India. 
 The DPRK team beat the Japanese 6:4 on 11m kick in the finals on November 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Asian Football Confederation gave award for a fair play to the DPRK team and award for best player to Kim Kum Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK team is qualified to participate in the World under-20 Soccer Championship to be held in Canada in 2007.

Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Introduced in U.S. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics posted several articles accompanied with photos showing the revolutionary activities of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il on its Internet homepage on the occasion of the 80th anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU).
 An article titled "80th Anniversary of DIU" noted that the programme of the DIU indicated to the Korean people the way of independent development, the path of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the last century, Kim Jong Il made a breakthrough towards the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, resolutely standing against the pressure of the imperialist allied forces under the uplifted banner of Songun held high by the DIU, it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An article titled "Songun, Invincible Banner for Accomplishing the Cause of Independence" said that Songun serves as a powerful weapon for the Korean people in carving out their own destiny in the strong spirit of national independence, adding that they have defended socialism despite all difficulties and trials as they have held high the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An article captioned "Korean People's Faith in Socialism" noted that the Korean people are working hard with confidence that they are sure to emerge victorious as long as they are led by Kim Jong Il. Their faith in socialism is based on the absolute trust in their leader and firm will to live, holding him in high esteem as their father at all times.

Hanchongryon Chairman Demands Prompt Stop to Expansion of U.S. Military Base 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- Jang Song Hoe, chairman of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon), on November 8 reportedly made public a statement titled "Stop the moves to expand the U.S. military base threatening peace of the Korean Peninsula and immediately release Chairman Kim Ji Thae".
 These moves to expand the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek are, to all intents and purposes, an offspring of the U.S. hostile policy towards the north and they pose a serious threat to peace on the Korean Peninsula, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the "Defense Ministry" threw additional barbed wire entanglements in the Phyongthaek area and the judicial authorities sentenced Kim Ji Thae to penal servitude, it went on: This is nothing but a despicable act to break the fighting spirit of the inhabitants and civic and public organizations that have turned out to check the expansion of the military base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Defense Ministry" aligning itself with the U.S. in its war machinations may temporarily go ahead with the expansion of the U.S. military base by forcible means. However, it can never break the will of the patriotic people who have risen up in the fight to defend peace on the Korean Peninsula, but will invite fiercer wrath and an all-people struggle.

Anti-U.S., Anti-War Slogans Issued in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly issued slogans calling upon all the people to turn out in the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle on Nov. 9.
 The slogans noted that the Korean Peninsula is in the grip of a crisis due to the U.S. war threat and economic plunder and if this U.S. policy of domination is tolerated, it will bring irrevocable disasters to the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The slogans appealed to one million of people to turn out in the anti-U.S., anti-war struggle in order to decisively smash the U.S. war moves, check the conclusion of the "south Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement" inviting a national ruin and build a new society where the people have become a master. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also urged the U.S. to immediately lift the groundless sanctions against the DPRK and abandon the policy of war against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all Koreans to pool their efforts for driving out foreign forces and achieving peace and co-prosperity.

Japan's Hostile Policy toward DPRK Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- There emerged a new government in Japan but its deplorable position as a servant of the U.S. and its political waiting maid can never change. This is a tragedy of Japan which it can never escape as long as it is in the pocket of its American master, observes Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed commentary.
 Japan is describing the application of the "financial sanctions" against the DPRK as "efforts" for what it called "dialogue" and has become more vociferous about "the abduction issue" while intensifying its suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan since the emergence of the new Cabinet, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe Cabinet's desperate hostile moves against the DPRK are nothing but despicable acts that can be perpetrated only by political charlatans loyal to the Uncle Sam. The Japanese militarists seized by the ambition for reinvasion are zealously cooperating with the U.S. in its moves to provoke a new Korean war and going crazy to please it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In a word, the new Japanese government has taken only actions to bedevil the DPRK-Japan relations since its emergence. The desperate political provocations made by Japan against the DPRK to seriously infringe upon its sovereignty and dignity have touched off indignation among the Korean people.  The Korean people accurately keep on record not only the crimes Japan committed in the past but those crimes being perpetrated by it at present. Growing stronger are the Korean people's resolution and will to force Japan to pay for all those crimes without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolhardy of Japan to eye a responsible post at the UN. No country will trust Japan as it is going reckless, just copying the behavior of its American master, still not free from the bad practice of kowtowing to the U.S. and toeing its line.

GNP's Ruckus of Confrontation with North under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The group of the "Grand National Party" of south Korea blustered that "sanctions against the north should be escalated" and "the south should show a resolute will" as part of their smear campaign against the north over its deterrent for self-defense. They went the lengths of letting loose vituperations that they should do the north serious disservice, while finding fault even with its social system without hesitation.
 Commenting on this, a news analyst of Rodong Sinmun Monday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP gentry is a group of traitors utterly indifferent to the fellow countrymen and the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war deterrent of the DPRK built under the great banner of Songun is, to all intents and purposes, to cope with the U.S. imperialists' moves to launch a nuclear war and invade the DPRK as it is a shield for just self-defense. It is also meant to protect south Korea, too, with warm compatriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP group is raising a hue and cry over the war deterrent of the north which protects them, too, while uttering no bad word about the nukes of the U.S. which threaten the nation. As if it were not enough with this, they are crying out for sanctions and calling for not ruling out even a war. This is nothing but a silly intention to respond to good will with evil one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These traitors are desperately insisting on suspending the tour of Mt. Kumgang and the project of the Kaesong industrial zone, icons of undertakings for national reconciliation and cooperation. They had better bear in mind who wished for them and who benefit from them before wagging their thin tongues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said behavior of the GNP teaches a lesson that this group of quislings hell-bent on confrontation with fellow countrymen and acts of treachery should be thrown overboard in order to frustrate the U.S. imperialists' moves for a war and achieve peace of the country and national reunification.

Songun Politics, Source of High National Self-Respect 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- Songun politics is the most powerful mode of politics in the 21st century, which is recognized by the whole world, and the Korean nation is a proud nation living in the great motherland of Songun, declares Rodong Sinmun Monday. 
 Noting that the self-respect of the Korean nation which has reached the highest phase in national history is a proud result of the invincible might of the Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea, the author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is the source of the growth of the Korean nation into a powerful one possessed of matchless war deterrent that can smash any aggressive force at one blow. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation is living as a dignified one which no formidable enemy dare provoke. This is because the DPRK has a mighty war deterrent which has been built by the Songun politics. The Songun politics of the WPK has brought up the Korean People's Army into a strong army in idea and faith and a matchless and ever-victorious powerful army possessed both of modern means of attack and defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invincible arms of Songun give confidence and courage, sweeping away the filth of flunkeyism and national nihilism remaining within the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The self-defensive defense capabilities of the DPRK serve as a powerful fortress of national defence and it has grown so mighty that even the U.S. imperialists boasting of the world's "strongest" military power dare not provoke it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics has ushered in the June 15 era of reunification in which the idea of "By our nation itself" is prevailing in the north and the south of Korea extending three thousand ri and is powerfully pushing forward its advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The arms of Songun representing patriotic will and indomitable spirit have made the Koreans hold high the banner of "By our nation itself" with national self-respect and confidence in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can vanquish the Korean nation which is fighting with pluck fearing nothing in the world and high national self-respect, conscious of its might.

Fair Solution to Mideast Issue Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The issue of Palestine and other Mideast issues should be fairly settled as required by the resolutions repeatedly adopted at the UN General Assembly sessions for several decades and international law on the basis of the agreement reached among member states under any circumstances. A DPRK representative clarified this stand during the discussion held on Nov. 8 on the "report of the Ad Hoc Committee for probing Israel's acts affecting the rights of the Palestinians in the occupied areas and other Arabs, " an agenda item of the meeting of the fourth Committee of the 61st UN General Assembly.
 The struggle of the Palestinians is a just struggle for recovering the usurped territories and winning back the right to national self-determination and vital right and the issue of Palestine is a regional and international matter directly linked with the issue of ensuring the Mideast peace, he noted, and went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A number of international measures have been taken to find a fair and peaceful settlement of the issue of Palestine and other Mideast issues but they have not been successfully implemented due to the expansionist policy and obstructions of the occupation forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that some forces are moving to delete items related to the Mideast from the agenda of the UN General Assembly as part of what they call UN reform in order to achieve their sinister aim to settle the above-said issues in their interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is unjustifiable as it is in contravention of the common desire of the international community to find a solution to the issues in the interests of the Palestinians and other Arabs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He reiterated the DPRK's firm solidarity with the Palestinians in their just struggle to win back their legitimate national rights and other Arab people in their efforts to find a fair solution to the Mideast issues.

New Casting Bonding and Heat Treatment Hardening Agent Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- University of Science in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has succeeded in developing a new kind of casting bonding and heat treatment hardening agent.
 The existing bonding and hardening agent is a chemical one, which is harmful to health. Its production cost is also high. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the newly developed agent is not made by chemical industrial method. Its production process is also simple and it is not detrimental to health in its production and use. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new one can be used as bonding and smearing agent in casting and hardening agent in heat treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has a good fluidity and its density is changeable so as to freely adjust the cooling speed. Its application makes it possible to minimize variation and enhance hardness during quenching metal products. It, therefore, considerably improves the mechanical character of products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When products are smeared with it, it prevents the oxidization and reduces chemical heat treatment process. It also raises the quality of processed metal goods such as gilding and elongation.

Central Zoo under Reconstruction
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- The Central Zoo at the foot of Mt. Taesong in Pyongyang, the DPRK, is being refurbished.
 The projects are being conducted in the direction of providing better living conditions to the animals to suit their physiological characteristics and of ensuring the best conveniences to the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reconstruction of elephant, giraffe, chimpanzee and many other animal cages is being vigorously carried on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new cages will be furnished with facilities to ensure temperature and ventilation in winter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Water project is also under way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ju Kum Chol, a section chief of the zoo, told KCNA that people would soon enjoy a good holiday in the renovated zoo.

U.S. Termed Chief Nuclear Criminal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- South Korea has turned into the biggest nuclear outpost in the Far East with stockpiles of more than 1,000 U.S. nuclear weapons of different types including A-bombs, nuclear shells and warheads, nuclear mines, backpack nukes and Neutron bombs and their delivery means. This fact clearly proves that the U.S. is chiefly to blame for having posed the threat of a nuclear war to the Korean Peninsula. 
 A spokesman for the Korean National Peace Committee declared this in a statement released on Nov. 13, 20 years since the U.S. announced that it would deploy in south Korea "Lance" missiles capable of carrying neutron bombs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was none other than the U.S. that introduced nukes into south Korea for the first time and turned it into a nuclear arsenal and a nuclear outpost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has barred the denuclearization of the peninsula and put the Korean nation in the constant danger of a nuclear war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite preposterous for the U.S. to take issue with the DPRK over its nuclear deterrent for just self-defence, while keeping mum about the criminal nuclear arms build-up it has perpetrated for years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is contemplating shipping into south Korea not only tactical nuclear weapons but strategic nuclear weapons in case of contingency on the Korean Peninsula, more frantically stepping up its moves for a nuclear war under the pretext of the DPRK's possession of nuclear deterrent. This patently proves that the U.S. nuclear ambition not only remains unchanged but poses an increasing danger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans should turn out in the struggle to frustrate the U.S. moves to stifle the DPRK and launch a nuclear war and stage fierce anti-U.S. resistance in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should drop its foolish aim to bring the Korean people to their knees and withdraw its forces and all its nuclear war equipment from south Korea without delay.

Reception Given on 50th Anniversary of Joson University
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 13 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the Keio Plaza Hotel in Tokyo on Nov. 10 in commemoration of the 50th anniversary of Joson University of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 Present at the reception were Chairman So Man Sul and Chief Vice-Chairman Ho Jong Man of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were Japanese political, academic, press, social and cultural figures and more than 300 foreign university personages in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jang Pyong Thae, rector of Joson University, in his speech noted that the educational aid fund and stipends remitted by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il in 152 installments were life-giving water for development of the university and the democratic national education of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Joson University has established the regular university educational system for half a century and steadily developed into a university of overseas compatriots which is making leaping progress in the 21st century, both in name and reality, thanks to the special loving care of Kim Jong Il and the wholehearted sincerity and support of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation is now complicated, but the future of the homeland is rosy and bright, he said, adding that Joson University will in the future, too, positively contribute to the prosperity and reunification of the homeland and friendship with universities of Japan and different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory speeches were made by Japanese public figures and congratulatory messages from foreign universities were introduced at the reception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants saw a video show on the 50 year-long development of Joson University.
